<!-- PART 1: GETTING STARTED -->
<h1>PART 1: GETTING STARTED</h1>

<h2>1.1 Introduction</h2>
<p>Welcome to Flow360, your complete fuel station management system. This software helps you manage:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Sales</strong> - Track all fuel and shop sales</li>
<li><strong>Inventory</strong> - Monitor stock levels and transfers</li>
<li><strong>Tanks</strong> - Manage fuel tanks and dip readings</li>
<li><strong>Shifts</strong> - Open and close cashier shifts</li>
<li><strong>Customers</strong> - Maintain customer records and loyalty</li>
<li><strong>Staff</strong> - Manage employees and their access</li>
<li><strong>Reports</strong> - Generate business insights and KRA compliance reports</li>
</ul>

<h2>1.2 Logging In</h2>
<h3>Web Application Login</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Open your web browser (Chrome, Firefox, or Edge recommended)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Go to your Flow360 website address</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter your <strong>Email Address</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter your <strong>Password</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Click the <strong>Login</strong> button</div>

<div class="note">
<strong>Note:</strong> If you forget your password, contact your administrator to reset it.
</div>

<h2>1.3 Understanding User Roles</h2>
<p>Flow360 has different user roles with different access levels:</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Role</th><th>Access Level</th><th>Can Use</th></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Vendor/Director</strong></td><td>Full access to all branches and HQ</td><td>Web App + Mobile App</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Manager</strong></td><td>Access to assigned branch only</td><td>Web App + Mobile App</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Supervisor</strong></td><td>Access to assigned branch only</td><td>Web App + Mobile App</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Cashier</strong></td><td>Sales transactions only</td><td>Mobile App ONLY</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning">
<strong>Important:</strong> Cashiers cannot log into the web application. They must use the mobile app on the Sunmi device.
</div>

<h2>1.4 Dashboard Overview</h2>
<p>After logging in, you will see the Dashboard. This shows a summary of your business:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Today's Sales</strong> - Total sales amount for today</li>
<li><strong>Total Customers</strong> - Number of registered customers</li>
<li><strong>Active Staff</strong> - Number of staff members</li>
<li><strong>Recent Transactions</strong> - Latest sales activities</li>
<li><strong>Sales Charts</strong> - Visual graphs of your sales trends</li>
</ul>

<h3>Navigation Menu</h3>
<p>The left side of the screen shows the main menu. Click on any menu item to go to that section:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Dashboard</strong> - Home page with summary</li>
<li><strong>Sales</strong> - View and manage sales</li>
<li><strong>Inventory</strong> - Manage stock items</li>
<li><strong>Tanks</strong> - Fuel tank management</li>
<li><strong>Customers</strong> - Customer database</li>
<li><strong>Staff</strong> - Employee management</li>
<li><strong>Reports</strong> - Business reports</li>
<li><strong>Loyalty</strong> - Loyalty program settings</li>
<li><strong>Payments</strong> - Payment records</li>
</ul>

<!-- PART 2: WEB APPLICATION GUIDE -->
<h1>PART 2: WEB APPLICATION GUIDE</h1>

<h2>2.1 Sales Management</h2>

<h3>Sales Summary Page</h3>
<p>This page shows all your sales for the current shift.</p>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Sales</strong> in the menu, then <strong>Sales Summary</strong></p>

<p><strong>What you can do:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>View total sales amount</li>
<li>See breakdown by fuel type</li>
<li>View individual transactions</li>
<li>End the current shift (see Shift Management section)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Automated Sales Report</h3>
<p>This shows sales from pump meters (bulk sales recorded automatically).</p>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Sales</strong> in the menu, then <strong>Automated Sales</strong></p>

<p><strong>Filtering Options:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fuel Type</strong> - Filter by specific fuel (Petrol, Diesel, etc.)</li>
<li><strong>Nozzle</strong> - Filter by pump nozzle number</li>
<li><strong>Payment Method</strong> - Cash, M-Pesa, Card, etc.</li>
<li><strong>Document Type</strong> - Invoice or Receipt</li>
<li><strong>Search</strong> - Search by invoice number</li>
</ul>

<h3>Creating an Invoice (Web)</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Go to <strong>Sales Summary</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Click <strong>Issue Invoice</strong> button</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Select the <strong>Customer</strong> (or leave as Walk-in)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Select the <strong>Product</strong> (fuel type)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Enter the <strong>Quantity</strong> in litres</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Select the <strong>Nozzle</strong> used</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">7</span>Choose <strong>Payment Method</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">8</span>Click <strong>Submit</strong></div>

<div class="tip">
<strong>Tip:</strong> The system automatically updates the nozzle meter reading after each sale.
</div>

<h2>2.2 Inventory Management</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Inventory</strong> in the menu</p>

<h3>Viewing Inventory</h3>
<p>The inventory page shows all your products and their current stock levels:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Item Name</strong> - Product name</li>
<li><strong>Item Code</strong> - Unique product code</li>
<li><strong>Current Stock</strong> - Available quantity</li>
<li><strong>Unit Price</strong> - Selling price</li>
<li><strong>Category</strong> - Product category</li>
</ul>

<h3>Stock Updates</h3>
<p>Stock levels are updated automatically through:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Purchase Deliveries</strong> - When you receive stock from suppliers</li>
<li><strong>Stock Transfers</strong> - When stock moves between branches</li>
<li><strong>Shift Endings</strong> - When you enter tank dip readings</li>
</ul>

<div class="warning">
<strong>Important:</strong> Manual stock adjustments have been disabled to ensure accurate tracking. Stock can only change through the methods listed above.
</div>

<h2>2.3 Tank Management</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Inventory</strong> then <strong>Manage Tanks</strong></p>

<h3>Viewing Tanks</h3>
<p>This page shows all fuel tanks at your branch:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tank Name</strong> - Identification name (e.g., "Tank 1 - Petrol")</li>
<li><strong>Fuel Type</strong> - Type of fuel stored</li>
<li><strong>Capacity</strong> - Maximum tank capacity in litres</li>
<li><strong>Current Stock</strong> - Current fuel level in litres</li>
<li><strong>Fill Level</strong> - Percentage of tank filled</li>
</ul>

<h3>Adding a New Tank</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Click <strong>Add Tank</strong> button</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Enter the <strong>Tank Name</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Select the <strong>Fuel Type</strong> from the dropdown</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter the <strong>Capacity</strong> in litres</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Enter the <strong>Initial Stock</strong> level</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Click <strong>Save</strong></div>

<h3>Accepting Stock Transfers</h3>
<p>When another branch sends you fuel:</p>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>You will see a badge showing pending transfers</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Click <strong>Accept Transfer</strong> on the tank</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Select the transfer from the list</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Click <strong>Accept</strong> to receive the stock</div>

<h3>Sending Stock Transfers</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Click <strong>Transfer Stock</strong> on the tank you want to send from</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Select the <strong>Destination Branch</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Select the <strong>Destination Tank</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter the <strong>Quantity</strong> to transfer</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Click <strong>Transfer</strong></div>

<h2>2.4 Shift Management</h2>
<p>Shifts track all sales activities between shift open and close times.</p>

<h3>Starting a Shift</h3>
<p>Shifts are started automatically when a cashier logs in, or you can manually open one:</p>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Go to <strong>Sales Summary</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>If no shift is active, click <strong>Start Shift</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter opening <strong>Float Amount</strong> (cash in drawer)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Confirm the <strong>Opening Meter Readings</strong> for each nozzle</div>

<h3>Ending a Shift</h3>
<p>At the end of your work period:</p>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Go to <strong>Sales Summary</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Click <strong>End Shift</strong> button</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter <strong>Closing Meter Readings</strong> for each nozzle</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter <strong>Tank Dip Readings</strong> (current fuel levels)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Review the calculated <strong>Bulk Sales</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Click <strong>Submit</strong></div>

<div class="note">
<strong>How Bulk Sales are Calculated:</strong><br>
The system calculates bulk sales using this formula:<br><br>
<strong>Bulk Sales = (Closing Reading - Opening Reading) - Invoiced Quantity</strong><br><br>
This represents fuel sold but not invoiced during the shift.
</div>

<h2>2.5 Customer Management</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Customers</strong> in the menu</p>

<h3>Viewing Customers</h3>
<p>See all registered customers with their details:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Customer Name</strong></li>
<li><strong>Phone Number</strong></li>
<li><strong>Email Address</strong></li>
<li><strong>KRA PIN</strong> (for business customers)</li>
<li><strong>Loyalty Points</strong></li>
</ul>

<h3>Adding a New Customer</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Click <strong>Add Customer</strong> button</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Enter the customer's <strong>Name</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter their <strong>Phone Number</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter their <strong>Email</strong> (optional)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>For business customers, enter their <strong>KRA PIN</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Click <strong>Save</strong></div>

<h3>Editing a Customer</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Find the customer in the list</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Click the <strong>Edit</strong> button (pencil icon)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Make your changes</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Click <strong>Save</strong></div>

<h2>2.6 Staff Management</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Staff</strong> in the menu</p>

<h3>Viewing Staff</h3>
<p>See all employees at your branch:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Name</strong> - Employee full name</li>
<li><strong>Email</strong> - Login email</li>
<li><strong>Role</strong> - Their job role (Manager, Supervisor, Cashier)</li>
<li><strong>Status</strong> - Active or Inactive</li>
</ul>

<h3>Adding New Staff</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Click <strong>Add Staff</strong> button</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Enter their <strong>Full Name</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter their <strong>Email Address</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Create a <strong>Password</strong> for them</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Select their <strong>Role</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Click <strong>Save</strong></div>

<div class="tip">
<strong>Tip:</strong> Give each staff member their own login. Never share passwords.
</div>

<h2>2.7 Reports</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Reports</strong> in the menu</p>

<p>Flow360 provides many reports to help you understand your business:</p>

<h3>Daily Sales Report</h3>
<p>Shows all sales for a selected date range.</p>
<ul>
<li>Select the <strong>Date Range</strong></li>
<li>Filter by <strong>Fuel Type</strong>, <strong>Payment Method</strong>, etc.</li>
<li>View totals and individual transactions</li>
<li>Export to Excel if needed</li>
</ul>

<h3>Nozzle Sales Report</h3>
<p>Shows sales broken down by individual pump nozzles.</p>
<ul>
<li>See which pumps are busiest</li>
<li>Track meter reading differences</li>
<li>Identify any discrepancies</li>
</ul>

<h3>Shift Reports</h3>
<p>Shows summary of each completed shift:</p>
<ul>
<li>Opening and closing times</li>
<li>Total sales per shift</li>
<li>Bulk sales calculated</li>
<li>Staff member who worked the shift</li>
</ul>

<h3>X-Report and Z-Report</h3>
<p>KRA compliance reports:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>X-Report</strong> - Mid-day summary (can run multiple times)</li>
<li><strong>Z-Report</strong> - End of day final report</li>
</ul>

<h3>Other Reports Available</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Report</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Sales Summary</td><td>Overall sales overview</td></tr>
<tr><td>Inventory Valuation</td><td>Value of current stock</td></tr>
<tr><td>Customer Statement</td><td>Customer transaction history</td></tr>
<tr><td>Aged Receivables</td><td>Outstanding customer payments</td></tr>
<tr><td>Aged Payables</td><td>Outstanding supplier payments</td></tr>
<tr><td>VAT Report</td><td>Tax summary for KRA</td></tr>
<tr><td>Excise Duty Report</td><td>Excise tax details</td></tr>
<tr><td>Profit &amp; Loss</td><td>Business profitability</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>2.8 Loyalty Program</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Loyalty</strong> in the menu</p>

<h3>How Loyalty Works</h3>
<p>Customers earn points on purchases and can redeem them for discounts.</p>
<ul>
<li>Set points earned per shilling spent</li>
<li>Set point value for redemption</li>
<li>View customer point balances</li>
<li>Track point transactions</li>
</ul>

<h3>Applying Loyalty Discounts</h3>
<p>When creating an invoice:</p>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Select the customer</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Their point balance will show</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Choose to <strong>Apply Points</strong> if desired</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Points are deducted from their balance</div>

<h2>2.9 Payments</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Payments</strong> in the menu</p>

<h3>Viewing Payment Records</h3>
<p>See all payment transactions:</p>
<ul>
<li>Payment date and time</li>
<li>Customer name</li>
<li>Amount paid</li>
<li>Payment method (Cash, M-Pesa, Card, Bank Transfer)</li>
<li>Reference number</li>
</ul>

<!-- PART 3: HEADQUARTERS FEATURES -->
<h1>PART 3: HEADQUARTERS (HQ) FEATURES</h1>

<p>These features are only available to <strong>Vendors</strong> and <strong>Directors</strong> who manage multiple branches.</p>

<h2>3.1 HQ Dashboard</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Headquarters</strong> in the menu</p>

<p>The HQ Dashboard shows:</p>
<ul>
<li>Combined sales across all branches</li>
<li>Branch performance comparison</li>
<li>Pending approvals</li>
<li>Stock levels across branches</li>
</ul>

<h2>3.2 Purchase Orders</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Headquarters</strong> then <strong>Purchase Orders</strong></p>

<h3>Creating a Purchase Order</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Click <strong>Create Purchase Order</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Select the <strong>Supplier</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Add items to the order with quantities and prices</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Optionally add <strong>Transporter</strong> details</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Enter <strong>Vehicle Registration</strong> and <strong>Driver</strong> details</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Submit the order</div>

<h3>Purchase Order Approval</h3>
<p>Orders must be approved by a Manager or Director before branches can receive them.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pending</strong> - Waiting for approval</li>
<li><strong>Approved</strong> - Ready for delivery</li>
<li><strong>Rejected</strong> - Not approved (with comments)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Receiving Deliveries (at Branch)</h3>
<p>When a fuel delivery arrives at the branch:</p>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Go to <strong>Purchases</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Find the approved purchase order</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Click <strong>Accept Delivery</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter <strong>Tank Volume Before</strong> delivery</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Enter <strong>Tank Volume After</strong> delivery</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Enter <strong>Dispenser Reading Before</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">7</span>Enter <strong>Dispenser Reading After</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">8</span>Enter <strong>Bowser Volume</strong> (tanker delivery amount)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">9</span>System calculates variance automatically</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">10</span>Click <strong>Confirm Delivery</strong></div>

<div class="note">
<strong>Variance Calculation:</strong><br>
Variance = ((Tank After - Tank Before) + (Dispenser After - Dispenser Before)) - Bowser Volume<br><br>
A negative variance indicates loss. A positive variance indicates gain.
</div>

<h2>3.3 Approvals</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Headquarters</strong> then <strong>Approvals</strong></p>

<p>Review and approve pending requests:</p>
<ul>
<li>Purchase orders awaiting approval</li>
<li>Stock transfer requests</li>
<li>Staff access requests</li>
</ul>

<h2>3.4 Supplier Management</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Headquarters</strong> then <strong>Suppliers</strong></p>

<h3>Adding a Supplier</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Click <strong>Add Supplier</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Enter <strong>Supplier Name</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter <strong>Contact Person</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter <strong>Phone Number</strong> and <strong>Email</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Enter <strong>KRA PIN</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Click <strong>Save</strong></div>

<h2>3.5 Items Catalog</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Headquarters</strong> then <strong>Items</strong></p>

<p>Manage all products sold across your branches from one place:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add new items to the catalog</li>
<li>Set default prices</li>
<li>Assign items to specific branches with custom pricing</li>
<li>View which branches have which items</li>
</ul>

<h3>Assigning Items to Branches</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Find the item in the catalog</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Click <strong>Assign to Branch</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Select the branch</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Set the branch-specific price</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Click <strong>Assign</strong></div>

<h2>3.6 Staff Management (HQ)</h2>
<p><strong>How to access:</strong> Click <strong>Headquarters</strong> then <strong>Staff Management</strong></p>

<p>Manage staff across all branches:</p>
<ul>
<li>View staff at all branches</li>
<li>Transfer staff between branches</li>
<li>Change roles and permissions</li>
<li>Activate or deactivate accounts</li>
</ul>

<!-- PART 4: MOBILE APP GUIDE -->
<h1>PART 4: MOBILE APP (APK) GUIDE</h1>

<p>The Flow360 mobile app is designed for Sunmi V2S POS devices used by cashiers at the fuel station.</p>

<h2>4.1 Installing the App</h2>
<p>The app is pre-installed on your Sunmi device. If you need to reinstall:</p>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Download the APK file from your administrator</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Open the file on the Sunmi device</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Tap <strong>Install</strong> when prompted</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Wait for installation to complete</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>Tap <strong>Open</strong> to start the app</div>

<h2>4.2 Logging In</h2>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Open the Flow360 app</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Enter your <strong>Email Address</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Enter your <strong>Password</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Tap <strong>Login</strong></div>

<div class="note">
<strong>Note:</strong> Your login credentials are provided by your supervisor or manager. Keep them secure and do not share with anyone.
</div>

<h2>4.3 Dashboard</h2>
<p>After logging in, you see the Dashboard screen:</p>

<h3>Dashboard Shows:</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Today's Sales</strong> - Your total sales for today</li>
<li><strong>Number of Transactions</strong> - How many sales you've made</li>
<li><strong>Current Shift Status</strong> - If you're in an active shift</li>
<li><strong>Quick Actions</strong> - Buttons to create invoice or view history</li>
</ul>

<h3>Bottom Navigation</h3>
<p>At the bottom of the screen are tabs:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Home</strong> - Dashboard screen</li>
<li><strong>Invoice</strong> - Create new invoice</li>
<li><strong>History</strong> - View past sales</li>
<li><strong>Products</strong> - View available products</li>
</ul>

<h2>4.4 Creating Invoices</h2>
<p>This is the main function for cashiers - recording fuel sales.</p>

<h3>Creating a New Invoice</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Tap <strong>Invoice</strong> at the bottom menu (or <strong>Create Invoice</strong> on dashboard)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>Customer Selection:
<ul>
<li>For walk-in customers: Leave as "Walk-in Customer"</li>
<li>For registered customers: Tap <strong>Select Customer</strong> and search by name or phone</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Select the <strong>Product</strong> (fuel type: Petrol, Diesel, Kerosene)</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">4</span>Enter the <strong>Quantity</strong> in litres</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">5</span>The <strong>Price</strong> is calculated automatically</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">6</span>Select the <strong>Nozzle</strong> number used</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">7</span>Select <strong>Payment Method</strong>:
<ul>
<li>Cash</li>
<li>M-Pesa</li>
<li>Card</li>
<li>Bank Transfer</li>
<li>Credit (for approved customers only)</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">8</span>Tap <strong>Create Invoice</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">9</span>The invoice is sent to KRA and a receipt prints automatically</div>

<h3>Invoice Confirmation</h3>
<p>After creating an invoice, you will see:</p>
<ul>
<li>Invoice number</li>
<li>KRA receipt number (SCU No.)</li>
<li>Customer name</li>
<li>Amount</li>
<li>Option to print another copy</li>
</ul>

<div class="warning">
<strong>Important:</strong> Always verify the customer receives their receipt. The receipt contains the KRA fiscal number needed for tax compliance.
</div>

<h2>4.5 Viewing Sales History</h2>
<p>View all your sales transactions.</p>

<h3>Accessing History</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Tap <strong>History</strong> at the bottom menu</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>See list of all your transactions</div>

<h3>History Shows:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Invoice number</li>
<li>Date and time</li>
<li>Customer name</li>
<li>Product sold</li>
<li>Quantity</li>
<li>Amount</li>
<li>Payment method</li>
</ul>

<h3>Viewing Invoice Details</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Tap on any transaction in the list</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>See full invoice details</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">3</span>Tap <strong>Print</strong> to reprint the receipt</div>

<h2>4.6 Products List</h2>
<p>View all products available for sale.</p>

<h3>Accessing Products</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">1</span>Tap <strong>Products</strong> at the bottom menu</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-number">2</span>See list of all products</div>

<h3>Products Shows:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Product name</li>
<li>Product code</li>
<li>Current price per litre</li>
<li>Category</li>
</ul>

<div class="note">
<strong>Note:</strong> You cannot change prices from the mobile app. Price changes are made by managers through the web application.
</div>

<!-- PART 5: TROUBLESHOOTING -->
<h1>PART 5: TROUBLESHOOTING</h1>

<h2>Common Problems and Solutions</h2>

<h3>Problem: Cannot Login</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
<tr><td>Wrong password</td><td>Double-check your password. Passwords are case-sensitive.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Account deactivated</td><td>Contact your manager to reactivate your account.</td></tr>
<tr><td>No internet connection</td><td>Check your WiFi or mobile data connection.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cashier trying web login</td><td>Cashiers can only use the mobile app, not the website.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Problem: Invoice Not Printing</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
<tr><td>Printer out of paper</td><td>Replace the receipt paper roll.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Printer cover not closed</td><td>Close the printer cover firmly until it clicks.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Device needs restart</td><td>Turn the Sunmi device off and on again.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Problem: KRA Error When Creating Invoice</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
<tr><td>Internet connection lost</td><td>Check your internet connection and try again.</td></tr>
<tr><td>KRA server down</td><td>Wait a few minutes and try again. If problem persists, contact support.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Invalid customer KRA PIN</td><td>Verify the customer's KRA PIN is correct.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Problem: Cannot See Stock Levels</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
<tr><td>Not synced</td><td>Refresh the page by pulling down or clicking refresh button.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Permission issue</td><td>Cashiers cannot view stock. Ask your supervisor.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Problem: Transfer Not Showing</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
<tr><td>Not yet sent</td><td>Confirm with sending branch that transfer was completed.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Wrong tank selected</td><td>Check if transfer was sent to a different tank.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Getting Help</h2>
<p>If you cannot resolve a problem:</p>
<ol>
<li>Note down the exact error message you see</li>
<li>Take a screenshot if possible</li>
<li>Contact your supervisor or manager</li>
<li>If they cannot help, contact Flow360 support with the error details</li>
</ol>

<h2>Quick Reference: Daily Workflow</h2>

<h3>Start of Day (Cashier)</h3>
<ol>
<li>Log into the mobile app</li>
<li>Confirm your shift is active</li>
<li>Check opening meter readings match your records</li>
<li>Begin serving customers</li>
</ol>

<h3>During the Day (Cashier)</h3>
<ol>
<li>Create invoice for each sale</li>
<li>Give receipt to customer</li>
<li>Handle cash/M-Pesa/card payments</li>
<li>Report any issues to supervisor</li>
</ol>

<h3>End of Day (Supervisor/Manager)</h3>
<ol>
<li>Go to Sales Summary on web app</li>
<li>Click End Shift</li>
<li>Enter closing meter readings for each nozzle</li>
<li>Enter tank dip readings</li>
<li>Review bulk sales calculation</li>
<li>Submit to close the shift</li>
</ol>

